latestIgtvVideos.title: How i cleared my skin with @palmersuk
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#ad 
My current morning skincare routine with @palmersuk 
This is also my current PM routine. 
 
Recently I had an unknown allergic reaction on my skin, therefore I had to change my skincare routine and currently sticking to naturally inspired products to help with recovery and it’s going really well. 
Since I am using the  @palmersuk New Coconut Oil Formula Facial Care Range, I have seen a huge improvement in my skin, my skin is cleared up from my rashes, and my scars are slowly fading. 
This range has Coconut Oil which is loaded with naturally occurring healthy skin and hair components. 
Did you know Coconut Oil also contains a high level of medium-chain fatty acids which create a breathable protective barrier that helps lock in moisture to prevent skin dehydration?
And natural antioxidants in these products help combat the effects of ageing by preventing free radical damage. Vitamin E and proteins rejuvenate and soothe skin.
Palmer’s raw, extra virgin coconut oil is ethically and sustainably sourced. This range is available to buy @tescofood @amazon.

latestIgtvVideos.title: 15 mins instant pot creamy cauliflower chicken curry (9+months)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys 
Hope you enjoy this simple and easy recipe and comment below if you like video like this. Please bare with me this is something new so I need figure out how I can film it better way in the future💗🥰
Ayaan loves this sort of curry style with his rice , couscous and pasta 
Ingredients
1/2 chopped cauliflower 
1 large chopped chicken breast 
I used ghee but you can use oil or butter 
1/2 chopped onion 
1 chopped tomato 
Few garlic cloves 
Little bit of Cinnamon powder 
Little bit of turmeric powder 
1/2 water 
1/2 cup of coconut milk ( optional) 
You can add as many veg you want like carrot , beans , potatoes and you can avoid chicken if you are prefer to be veg only.
I normally switch up the veg every time I make to introduce new flavours and taste to Ayaan.
this defo can be adult curry, add some green chilies and salt and enjoy it with hot plate of rice 🥰
